    <text id="B0281T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Goodloe forwards information about a Lewis Lurner on to Jackson, as a claim was
                    filed against Turner at the Bureau.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Adams Express Company,<lb/>Great Eastern, Western &amp; Southern<lb/>Express
                    Forwarders.
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-11-02"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 2d 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Goshen [Bridge]</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I <abbr expan="received">recd</abbr> a letter from you a few days ago wishing to
                    know if I knew Lewis Lurner and if he had any Property. I know him he is living
                    with me and Draws his pay as fast as he earns it to pay up last years <abbr
                        expan="receipts">recpts</abbr> he has nothing that I know of. I told him you
                    had a Claim in your hand against him he said there was some owing of him and he
                    would have to push them to pay you.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">H. A. Goodloe</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
